div.p:
Commodity component agreement (all in millions dollars) is cotton 16;
                            dairy products 3; edible fats and oils 1; tobacco .6; dry fruit .2;
                            ocean transportation .9; total 21.7. Burma asked why we omitted wheat
                            and informed that US has no wheat history in Burma and US does not wish
                            to appear attempting displace Burma’s normal purchases of flour. Burma
                            conceded US has real problem Australia.
